The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Sunday, December 08, 2002 				 Bangla take on resurgent WI
																								Dhaka, Dec. 7 (AFP): Bangladesh, with an uninspiring record of losing 14 Test matches out of 15 played, host a resurgent West Indies tomorrow in the first Test match between the two teams.																								After a ODI series win in India, the Carribeans continued their spree here, wrapping up the three-match one-day series 2-0 with the first game washed out by rain in Chittagong.																								Former captains Aminul Islam and Naimur Rehman were included in a 15-member Bangladesh squad for the two Tests on Thursday. 
